Examples


data("credit_woe")

m <- glm(bad ~ ., family = binomial, data = head(credit_woe, 10000))
m <- featsel_stepforward(m, scale = 5, trace = 0)

dnew <- tail(credit_woe, 10000)

gg_model_roc(m)

gg_model_roc(m, newdata = dnew, size = 2)


gg_model_ks(m)

gg_model_ks(m, newdata = dnew, size = 2)

gg_model_corr(m)

gg_model_importance(m)

#> Preparation of a new explainer is initiated
#>   -> model label       :  lm  (  default  )
#>   -> data              :  10000  rows  6  cols 
#>   -> data              :  tibble converted into a data.frame 
#>   -> target variable   :  10000  values 
#>   -> predict function  :  yhat.glm  will be used (  default  )
#>   -> predicted values  :  No value for predict function target column. (  default  )
#>   -> model_info        :  package stats , ver. 4.1.0 , task classification (  default  ) 
#>   -> predicted values  :  numerical, min =  0.03852792 , mean =  0.199 , max =  0.5331556  
#>   -> residual function :  difference between y and yhat (  default  )

#>   A new explainer has been created!
